Core inflation, which excludes the prices of food, non-alcoholic beverages, petrol and energy, rose to 4.3% year-on-year from 4.2%. JOHANNESBURG - South Africaâ€™s headline consumer inflation quickened to 5.1% year-on-year in July from 4.6% in June, data from Statistics South Africa showed on Wednesday. On a month-on-month basis, inflation rose to 0.8% in July from 0.4% in June. Core inflation, which excludes the prices of food, non-alcoholic beverages, petrol and energy, rose to 4.3% year-on-year from 4.2%, while on a month-on-month basis it increased to 0.6% from 0.2% previously.